The paper discusses the ability of deep neural networks to generalize well in the overparameterized regime, which is a topic of interest in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on autoencoders, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the inductive bias of autoencoders, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
